<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<TcPlcObject Version="1.1.0.1">
  <POU Name="FB_CheckPositionStateWrite" Id="{4a237718-942d-465c-a0b3-3b5d567db752}" SpecialFunc="None">
    <Declaration><![CDATA[(*
    OBSOLETE under the LCLS_Tc_Motion (ND) framework. File kept on disk for
    history; excluded from Library.plcproj so it does not compile.

    Why obsolete: this helper existed to mediate a race between PLC defaults
    and EPICS-side writes to ST_PositionState fields. The legacy idiom in the
    device FBs was "check bHadWrite; if no EPICS write happened this cycle,
    overwrite the slot from PLC staging vars; otherwise let the operator edit
    stand." That race no longer exists in the new framework:

      1. All ST_PositionState EPICS-facing fields (sName, fPosition,
         nEncoderCount, bMoveOk) carry pytmc "io: i" : read-only from EPICS.
         The remaining state fields (fDelta, bLocked, bValid, bUseRawCounts,
         bUpdated, stPMPS) have no pytmc pragma at all. There is no path for
         an operator to write to a position state from EPICS in the ND
         framework. The "from EPICS" half of the legacy race is gone.

      2. Motion-tuning fields the legacy helper compared (fVelocity, fAccel,
         fDecel) were removed from ST_PositionState : they live on the drive
         layer now (FB_MotionStageNC.MotionCmd, set via SetMotionParam()).

      3. The "apply PLC defaults once, then leave alone" job is owned by
         FB_StateConfigurator / FB_StateSetup, gated by the per-slot
         bUpdated latch that FB_PositionStateInternalND sets after first
         full configuration. Cyclic calls become no-ops automatically;
         re-application is the explicit knob bForceUpdate := TRUE.

    Net: the helper's premise (mediate concurrent PLC/EPICS writers) is
    structurally unrepresentable in the ND framework, and the framework
    provides a stricter, finer-grained mechanism for the same intent. No
    device FB should call this in migrated code.

    Original 1-D contract preserved below verbatim for reference only.
*)
FUNCTION_BLOCK FB_CheckPositionStateWrite
(*
    Save a position state during one cycle, then check it the next cycle
*)
VAR_IN_OUT
    astPositionState: ARRAY[1..GeneralConstants.MAX_STATES] OF ST_PositionState;
END_VAR
VAR_INPUT
    bCheck: BOOL;
    bSave: BOOL;
END_VAR
VAR_OUTPUT
    bHadWrite: BOOL;
END_VAR
VAR
    astCache: ARRAY[1..GeneralConstants.MAX_STATES] OF ST_PositionState;
    nIter: UINT;
END_VAR
]]></Declaration>
    <Implementation>
      <ST><![CDATA[
bHadWrite := FALSE;
IF bCheck THEN
    FOR nIter := 1 TO GeneralConstants.MAX_STATES DO
        // Only the runtime-editable EPICS fields
        bHadWrite S= astPositionState[nIter].sName <> astCache[nIter].sName;
        bHadWrite S= astPositionState[nIter].fPosition <> astCache[nIter].fPosition;
        bHadWrite S= astPositionState[nIter].fDelta <> astCache[nIter].fDelta;
        bHadWrite S= astPositionState[nIter].fVelocity <> astCache[nIter].fVelocity;
        bHadWrite S= astPositionState[nIter].fAccel <> astCache[nIter].fAccel;
        bHadWrite S= astPositionState[nIter].fDecel <> astCache[nIter].fDecel;
    END_FOR
END_IF

IF bSave THEN
    astCache := astPositionState;
END_IF]]></ST>
    </Implementation>
  </POU>
</TcPlcObject>